es their simple origin to the extreme forms some take today, delving into the murky subculture that has deliberately made them impenetrably obscure. Uniquely, it combines detailed technical expertise (regulatory regimes, financial crime, legal and equitable structuring) with an analysis of their impact on domestic and global political, economic, environmental and social concerns. An Anatomy of Tax Havens is a fascinating, informative read for a broad readership; from legal, accountancy and tax practitioners to compliance regulators, law enforcement agencies, and students and researchers interested in business studies, taxation, and crime.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aTax havenszCaribbean Area. 0aTax havenszEurope. 0aTax havenszUnited States. 4aRegulierung. 4aSteuerflucht. 4aSteuerhinterziehung. 4aSteueroasen. 4aVermögensungleichheit. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Taxation / General.2bisacsh  aAccountability.  aBeneficial Ownership Avoidance.  aHuman Rights.  aSecrecy.  aUnited States of America.  aWealth Inequality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2023 Englishz978311131907008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2023z9783111318134oZDB-23-DBV0 cEPUBz97831109851600 cprintz978311099667840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311098510840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110985108423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110985108/original  a978-3-11-131907-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMP